[1] Case update
- Sun 14 Jun 2020. CMRE (Comite Multisectoriel de la Riposte a la maladie a virus Ebola)
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://mailchi.mp/6b8f4307b577/ebola-situation-pidmiologique-du-14-juin-2020?e=6a8e4f1f4d

The epidemiological situation of the ebolavirus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 13 Jun 2020:
- Since the start of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases has been 3463, 3317 confirmed and 146 probable. In total, there have been 2280 deaths (2134 confirmed and 146 probable) and 1171 who have survived;
- 398 suspected cases are under investigation;
- No new confirmed case has been recorded for the 47th consecutive day
- No confirmed case is hospitalized in a CTE since the resurgence of the Ebola virus disease epidemic in Beni on 10 Apr 2020.

Epidemiological situation In the Province of Equateur on 13 June 2020:
-Since the start of the epidemic declared on 1 Jun 2020, the cumulative number of cases has been 17, including 14 confirmed and 3 probable. In total, there have been 11 deaths (8 confirmed and 3 probable);
- No new confirmed cases;
- No new deaths among the confirmed cases.

Vaccination
-----------
9560 people were vaccinated, from 14 Feb --10 Apr 2020, with the 2nd dose of the 2nd Ad26.ZEBOV / MVA-BN-Filo vaccine (Johnson & Johnson) in the 2 health areas from Karisimbi to Goma;
- 20 339 people were vaccinated until 29 Feb 2020, with the 2nd vaccine d26.ZEBOV / MVA-BN-Filo (Johnson & Johnson) in the 2 health areas from Karisimbi to Goma;
- A total of 2129 people were vaccinated from 11 Apr - 20 May 2020 around the resurgent cases of Beni;
- Since the start of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018 with the rVSV-ZEBOV vaccine 303 905 people have been vaccinated until 20 May 2020;
- Approved on 22 Oct 2019 by the Ethics Committee of the School of Public Health at the University of Kinshasa and on 23 Oct 2019 by the National Ethics Committee, the 2nd vaccine, called Ad26.ZEBOV / MVA-BN -Filo, is produced by Janssen Pharmaceuticals for Johnson & Johnson;
-This new vaccine complements the 1st, rVSV-ZEBOV, a vaccine used until then (since 8 Aug 2018) in this epidemic manufactured by the pharmaceutical group Merck, after approval by the Ethics Committee on 20 May 2018. It was recently pre-qualified for certification.

Entry point surveillance
------------------------
Since the start of the epidemic, the cumulative number of travelers checked (temperature taking) at health checkpoints, until 9 Jun 2020 is 179 635 921;
- To date, a total of 50 entry points (PoE) and health control points (PoC) are operational out of the 109 set up in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri in order to protect large cities in the country and to avoid the spread of the epidemic in neighboring countries.

